title: For Sale:  Unfired Glock 23 .40 3rd Gen OD Green
postcontent:
Unfired Glock 23 .40 cal in OD with 2 13 rd mags, 3rd generation, manufactured Oct/2009. Private face to face sale to WI resident. $550 price is not negotiable. I already paid tax and call in fee so you won't have to. Janesville

Probably the best trained defensive shooter in the country, Dr. Ignatius Piazza
chooses and carries "Glock".

http://frontsight.com/newsletter/html/17-right-gun.html 

 I will tell it to you straight because Front Sight does not sell guns in our pro shop.  We have no beneficial interest in any gun manufacturer and there is no "Front Sight Service Pistol" being promoted to anyone.  We are as pure as the driven snow as far as our interest in directing you to what is the best choice for a simple, reliable, and easy to use handgun that carries lots of fight-stopping cartridges.

Simplicity: The Glock is by far the simplest.  Trigger, magazine release, and slide release.  That's it.  The Glock is as simple as it gets. What about the Safety? Glocks have a safety on the trigger.  Safety is between your ears, so keep your finger out of the trigger guard until your sights are on the target.  We train YOU to be safe with ANY gun. We routinely place Glocks in the hands of students taking our courses who have never shot a gun before and they do extremely well with them and are extremely safe with them. 

Ease of use:  The Glock wins again with a trigger press that is essentially the same with each shot and has no safety lever to engage.

Accuracy:  Accuracy is really about YOU and not the gun.  Consistency is a better term to describe the gun.  Put the gun in a vice. How consistent is it in shooting a tight group?   You cannot hold the gun as steady as a vice, so all modern handguns are more consistent than you can accurately hold them.  If you can't shoot a tight group it is not the handgun.  The good news is we can train you to shoot accurately up to the consistency of your gun.

Speed:  Glock wins again.  The less you have to do to shoot the gun, the smoother and faster it is to deliver a fight-stopping hit. When we teach you how to properly re-rest the trigger for your second and subsequent shots, you will be amazed at how fast you can shoot an auto-loading pistol ACCURATELY.

So what do I carry? I can carry and shoot any gun extremely well.  I choose to carry. a Glock.  Why? Because in a gun fight, I too will only be half as good and half as smart as I am on my best day on the training range due to the stress of a lethal encounter.  Fortunately, a "half as good" Four Weapons Combat Master is still miles above the average dirtbag predator on his best day.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Hunters and Land Owners Needed
postcontent:
ATTENTION

Hunters and Land Owners Needed

Handi-Capable Outdoors is looking for hunters and land owners We are just starting out with this video for the disabled outdoorsman it has been in the works for a little over 2 years now, we just want to show the side of hunting that is rarely seen. We have six people on our staff five men and one women. Unfortunately we are all on fixed incomes an we can not afford to buy property or high priced hunts but we don't think that should stop us and neither should a disability. Our main goal is to show people with disabilities that they should not be lead to believe that they are handicapped but they are handicapable. Our primary choices of hunting will be archery shotgun muzzleloader rifle and pistol with whitetail deer eastern turkey waterfowl upland & migratory birds as well as varmint hunting . We hope to grow to broaden the horizon of hunters everywhere with this project. And hope that you join with us because we feel that if everyone would share the same philosophy and core values that we do together we can make the outdoor experience better for everyone. If you would like to help us in our endeavor weather it be to help with a hunt or to be a hunter or you have property and will allow us to hunt please contact me we can use all the help we can get.
Thank You & God Bless 
Handi-Capable Outdoors 
Contact Info 
Steven Dean 
REDACTED
REDACTED

This is an excellent condition G33/40 with single piece walnut stock. Receiver code 945 and dated 1940. Bolt is a correct G33/40 bolt with all correct G33/40 parts, but does not match the receiver. Stock, handguard, barrel, and rear sight leaf all have matching serial numbers. Stock is marked both on the comb of the butt and in the barrel channel. The only oddity exhibited on this gun is that someone put nail polish on either side of the front sight blade. It's covered by the front sight hood and could easily be removed. This a very very handsome G33/40 that would do any collection proud.

title: For Sale:  K31 Schmidt-Rubin rifle 7.5mm Swiss
postcontent:
This is a nice surplus K31 in 7.5x55 Swiss. This was the standard rifle of the Swiss army from 1933 to 1958. 

The rifle is a straight-pull bolt action with a detachable magazine. Magazines were typically one to a rifle and stripper clips were used for loading. 

Sportsmans Guide typically has the ammo for these. Clips also show up time to time at SG and other surplus vendors. 

I have never actually fired this gun. There are a few dings on the wood, seeing how it was in service for a while. The metal is in good shape, the finish is all there. All numbers match. The action operates smoothly. Very nice piece of Swiss machine work. By all accounts, the most accurate milsurp there is.

There is a tag under the buttplate with the name of the Swiss citizen who carried this rifle. I don't remember it now, I just looked at the tag and put it back.

I am looking to finance another gun, so trades are out at this time. 

Please have a valid Minnesota DL to show me at the time of sale.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus PT92c $250 OBO till tomorrow night then its gone
postcontent:
A refinished PT92c with 3 magazines 
Forjas Taurus finally entered the fray in 1991 by introducing its PT 92 Compact, better known as the PT 92C. This was created by cutting down the standard PT 92's barrel and slide by one inch and reducing the magazine capacity from 15 rounds to 13 and shortening the grip to match. Compared to the full-sized models the PT 92C lost three ounces, weighing 31 ounces without ammunition. To compete with Beretta's 8-shot Type M variant, Forjas Taurus eschewed further modification of the PT 92, instead introducing an altogether different l called the PT 908 in 1993.

postcontent:
A pre-packed Survival Vest that is a single unit that can be grabbed and put on quickly when you have to be on the move immediately.  It comes equipped with survival gear, 1st aid supplies and a two day supply of emergency food & water rations. Weighs approximately 22 lbs with the 2 liter hydration bladder empty.  Has an attached cross-draw holster for your sidearm (SIDEARM IN PHOTO NOT INCLUDED) and pouches for your spare mags.  Each Survival Vest can be customized. You can choose to change the configuration, add or omit certain survival gear or 1st Aid supplies. This option is especially handy for those wanting to spend less money.  We will try to work within a customer's budget to get them set up with a survival package.  Vest sizes are M/L (up to 44 inch chest) and XL/XXL (up to 52 inch chest).  Color options are Black, ACU, O.D. Green and Coyote Tan.  For detailed descriptions and photos of all survival gear and 1st aid supplies and other options go to:
    www.2012grab-n-gotacticalsurvivalvest.com.  
There is also available a 2012 Grab-N-Go Tactical Back Pack in ACU, Black, O.D. Green and Coyote Tan that comes equipped with all the gear and supplies that comes with the Survival Vest and it also can be customized.  FREE SHIPPING TO CONTINENTAL UNITED STATES - SHIPPING CHARGES APPLY TO ALASKA & HAWAII.
